README of offline/packages/crk/calib/align/RUN5

2005/11/20 
Susumu Oda, oda@cns.s.u-tokyo.ac.jp

1) RICHAlignment_track collects electron tracks and associated RICH PMT data,
   and saves them in a ROOT file. 
2) ProcessRing evaluates RICH mirror displacement parameters from the ROOT 
   file.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1)
RICHAlignment_track/RICHAlignment_track collects electron tracks and records 
projection points of the track at PC1 and PC3 using CNT nDSTs. It also records 
associated RICH PMT data using DSTs including CrkHit nodes.

Just do the followings to get a ROOT file; 
./autogen.sh
make
cd macro
ln -s ../.libs/librichalignment_track.so ./librichalignment_track.so
root -l -b -q rich_align_track_RUN5.C
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2)
ProcessRing/RICH_Alignment evaluates mirror displacement parameters using a 
RICHAlignment_track output, and outputs the parameters to a text file and 
displays ring images. 

Just do the followings to get an output text file;
make
cd macro
ln -s ../libRICH_Alignment.so ./libRICH_Alignment.so
root -l dstrun_align_RUN5.C
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
offline/packages/crk/calib/align/README
will help you to understand these alignment procedure. 
